<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-04-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="192" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-04-21"><hi rend="italic">April 21,
                            1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Draft of naval instructions forwarded by the dispatch bag to day. Please send
                        names of the United States vessels, and if possible their commanders,
                        designated to police North Pacific Ocean and Bering Sea.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>